[Measles appears to be re-emerging in Brazil, in spite of effective
vaccination campaigns. The newspaper Folha de Sao Paulo on 9 July 1997
reported that 1157 cases had occurred in the Sao Paulo metropolitan area,
the worst outbreak for the last 5 years with, according to the Minstry of
Health, cases being "exported" to the states of Bahia & Ceara - Mod.JW]
